{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10",
    "summary": "Source text for 4 Maccabees 10 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:1",
      "text": "Now this one endured this praiseworthy death. The third was brought along, and exhorted by many to taste and save his life.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:2",
      "text": "But he cried out and said, “Don’t you know that the father of those who are dead is my father also, and that the same mother bore me, and that I was brought up in the same way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:3",
      "text": "I don’t renounce the noble relationship of my kindred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:4",
      "text": "Now then, whatever instrument of vengeance you have, apply it to my body, for you aren’t able to touch my soul, even if you want to.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:5",
      "text": "But they, highly incensed at his boldness of speech, dislocated his hands and feet with racking engines, and wrenching them from their sockets, dismembered him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:6",
      "text": "They dragged around his fingers, his arms, his legs, and his ankles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:7",
      "text": "Not being able by any means to strangle him, they tore off his skin, together with the extreme tips of his fingers, and then dragged him to the wheel,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:8",
      "text": "around which his vertebral joints were loosened, and he saw his own flesh torn to shreds, and streams of blood flowing from his entrails.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:9",
      "text": "When about to die, he said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:10",
      "text": "“We, O accursed tyrant, suffer this for the sake of Divine education and virtue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:11",
      "text": "But you, for your impiety and blood shedding, will endure unceasing torments.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:12",
      "text": "Thus having died worthily of his kindred, they dragged forward the fourth, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:13",
      "text": "“Don’t share the madness of your kindred, but respect the king and save yourself.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:14",
      "text": "But he said to them, “You don’t have a fire so scorching as to make me play the coward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:15",
      "text": "By the blessed death of my kindred, and the eternal punishment of the tyrant, and the glorious life of the pious, I will not repudiate the noble brotherhood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:16",
      "text": "Invent, O tyrant, tortures, that you may learn, even through them, that I am the brother of those tormented before.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:17",
      "text": "When he had said this, the blood-thirsty, murderous, and unholy Antiochus ordered his tongue to be cut out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:18",
      "text": "But he said, “Even if you take away the organ of speech, God still hears the silent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:19",
      "text": "Behold, my tongue is extended, cut it off; for in spite of that you won’t silence our reasoning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:20",
      "text": "We gladly lose our limbs on behalf of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:fourth-maccabees.10.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "fourth-maccabees",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "4 Maccabees 10:21",
      "text": "But God will speedily find you, since you cut off the tongue, the instrument of divine melody.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
